<h1> GCSS Boundary Layer Cloud WG Home Page </h1>
<IMG SRC="xsmoke_LES.gif.pagespeed.ic.2Gwz-5Pk1E.png" width="288" height="288">
<p>

The <a href="http://www.gewex.org/gcss.html">GCSS</a> (<a href="http://www.gewex.org/">GEWEX</a> Cloud System Study) Boundary Layer Cloud Working
Group aims to improve physical parameterizations of clouds, other
boundary layer processes, and their interactions.  We
conduct careful intercomparisons between observational or laboratory
case studies, one-dimensional GCM single-column-model (SCM) results, and 3D
large-eddy-simulation models of cloud-topped boundary layers. Most of the
leading groups modelling boundary layer clouds have participated in
our annual workshops, held every 12-18 months.  The BLCWG is currently chaired by <A HREF="http://www.atmos.washington.edu/~breth/">Chris Bretherton</A>
(breth@atmos.washington.edu) of the Department of Atmospheric
Sciences, University of Washington, Seattle, WA, USA.
<p>
If you would like to keep in touch with our activities, you can join our email
list.  Our email address is gcss-l@phys.uu.nl. To join, send a message
containing the words
<p>
subscribe gcss-l
<p>
to server Majordomo@phys.uu.nl. To unsubscribe from the list, send this server
the message
<p>
unsubscribe gcss-l


<h3> Current GCSS BLCWG activities </h3>

<p> <b>Current DYCOMS RF02 nocturnal drizzling stratocumulus case</b> Preliminary results from this case were discussed in Athens. Final submissions following the slightly revised  <a href="http://sky.arc.nasa.gov:6996/ack/gcss9/index.html">LES</a>

    and <a href="GCSS1-RF02-SCM.html">SCM</a> case specifications are
    due <b>1 August 2005</b>.

<p><b>Pan-GCSS meeting, Athens, 16-20 May 2005</b>
<ul>
  <li><a href="GCSS1-200505-Athens/agenda.txt">Athens BLCWG meeting agenda</a>
  <li><a href="GCSS1-200505-Athens/talks.html">Talks</a> from BLCWG session
  <li><a href="GCSS1-200505-Athens/GCSS1_Athens_summary.ppt">Summary
  presentation </a> of BLCWG activities given at Athens.
</ul>

<h3> Related activities </h3> 
<ul>
  <li><a href="Arrowhead-200506/presentations.html">Presentations from Lake Arrowhead
    Workshop on the Planetary Boundary Layer</a>, 14-16 June 2005

  <li><a href="http://www.gewex.org/gabls.htm">GABLS </a>(the GEWEX Atmospheric 
  Boundary Layer Study), whose mission is to coordinate research on boundary 
  layer physics to improve the representation of the atmospheric boundary layer 
  in numerical models.<li>
  <a href="http://www.bom.gov.au/bmrc/wefor/staff/cnj/GCSS_pacific_case_final_files/frame.htm">
  GPCI</a> (the GCSS Pacific Cross-Section Intercomparison), which is comparing 
  the observed thermodynamic structure and clouds along a vertical cross-section 
  from the California coast to the central Pacific ITCZ during July 1998 and 
  2003 with simulations from regional and global simulations.
</ul>

