  <DD><STRONG>BOMEX Trade cumulus case</STRONG>. 
      July 1997, Seattle, WA, USA
  <DD><UL>
    <LI>Case Coordinator: Pier Siebesma, KNMI, Netherlands (siebesma@knmi.nl)

    <li><a HREF="http://ams.allenpress.com/amsonline/?request=get-abstract&issn=1520-0469&volume=060&issue=10&page=1201">
Siebesma, A. P., and coauthors, 2003:</a> A
large-eddy simulation intercomparison study of shallow cumulus
convection. <i>J. Atmos. Sci.</i>, <b>60</b>, 1201-1219.

    <LI><A HREF="http://www.knmi.nl/~siebesma/gcss/bomex.html">Case summary and goals, detailed case specifications, and preliminary results.</A>

    <LI><A HREF="BOMEX/trade.mpg">Animation</A> of cloud top heights
	from a BOMEX trade cumulus simulation on an approximately 25
	by 25 km domain using 256x256x72 gridpoints and a 100 m
	horizontal and 50 m vertical grid spacing, made by Dave
	Stevens of Lawrence Berkeley Labs. Blue cloudtops are at 600
	m, just above the subcloud lifted condensation level, and red
	corresponds to about 2 km cloud tops. Note range of cloud top
	heights.
	
  </UL>

